# hulibaza — shipped default allow (the built-in .hulibazaallow).
#
# Extensions treated as KNOWN TEXT: parsed as UTF-8 and given the larger
# size_cap_text_bytes instead of the small "other" cap. One extension per
# line, leading dot, case-insensitive; `#` comments. A per-section
# .hulibazaallow EXTENDS this list.
#
# Curation rule: ONLY extensions that are unambiguously text. Anything that
# also names a common BINARY format is deliberately EXCLUDED and handled via
# the sniffed "other" tier — e.g. .ts (MPEG transport stream), .doc/.docx and
# other office formats, .dat, .bin, media/image formats. .pdf is handled
# separately as a known-binary format with a dedicated parser.

